Description: Earring; bronze; circular, open-work; large incomplete loop; in the centre a cross with looped terminals enclosed by a border of looped V-shapes.
Curator's comments: Parallels: Flinders Petrie, Objects of Daily Use (London 1927) p. 14 and pl. x.244-249; J. Strzygowski, Koptische Kunst (Vienna 1904) cat. 7039; A. Drandaki, "Copper Alloy Jewellery at the Benaki Museum: 4th to 7th Century", Antiquité Tardive 13 (2005) 65-76, esp. 65-66.
Acquisition name: Donated by: British School of Archaeology, Egypt
